### 456.

That part of a tree which has shadow for background, is all of one tone,
and wherever the trees or branches are thickest they will be darkest,
because there are no little intervals of air. But where the boughs lie
against a background of other boughs, the brighter parts are seen
lightest and the leaves lustrous from the sunlight falling on them.

